source.buildSpec:
version: 0.2
phases:
  install:
    commands:
      - aws s3 cp s3://uno-beta-sdk/c2j-output-2021-01-11/cloudformation/2010-05-15/service-2.json /tmp/
      - aws configure add-model --service-model "file:///tmp/service-2.json" --service-name uno
      - pip3 install cloudformation-cli cloudformation-cli-go-plugin cfn-lint "pyyaml>=5.4"
  build:
    commands:
      - export REGIONS=$(aws ec2 describe-regions --query 'Regions[?OptInStatus!=`not-opted-in`].RegionName' --output text)
      - # export REGIONS=us-east-1  # remove this once public registry is available in all regions
      - export REGIONS="us-east-1 eu-central-1 us-east-1 us-east-2 eu-north-1 ap-south-1 eu-west-1 eu-west-2 eu-west-3"
      - # WORK: us-east-1 eu-central-1 us-east-1 us-east-2 eu-north-1 ap-south-1 eu-west-1 eu-west-2 eu-west-3
      - # DOESN'T WORK: ap-northeast-3
      - # "us-west-2"
      - # "ap-northeast-2 ap-northeast-1 sa-east-1 ca-central-1 ap-southeast-2"
      - # "eu-north-1 ap-south-1 eu-west-3 eu-west-2 eu-west-1 ap-northeast-3 ap-northeast-2 ap-northeast-1 sa-east-1 ca-central-1 ap-southeast-1 ap-southeast-2 eu-central-1 us-east-1 us-east-2 us-west-1 us-west-2"
      - echo $REGIONS
      - cd $(echo ${BUILD_DIRS} | awk '{print $1}')
      - aws s3 ls s3://${BUCKET} || aws s3 mb s3://${BUCKET}
      - wget -O eks-deploy.template.yaml https://raw.githubusercontent.com/aws-quickstart/quickstart-amazon-eks-cluster-resource-provider/main/deploy.template.yaml
      - |
        echo "creating iam roles if needed...."
        for r in ${REGIONS}; do
          role="$(aws iam list-roles --query 'Roles[?RoleName==`eks-cluster-execution`].RoleName' --output text)"
          if [  "$role" == "" ] ; then
            echo "Role not found in $r, creating"
            aws cloudformation create-stack --stack-name awsqs-eks-cluster --template-body file://eks-deploy.template.yaml --capabilities CAPABILITY_NAMED_IAM --region ${r}
            aws cloudformation wait stack-create-complete --stack-name awsqs-eks-cluster --region ${r}
          else
            echo "Found role $role in region $r"
          fi
        done
      - |
        echo "registering AWSQS::EKS::Cluster resource types..."
        for r in ${REGIONS}; do
          type="$(aws cloudformation list-types --region $r --query 'TypeSummaries[?TypeName==`AWSQS::EKS::Cluster`].TypeName' --output text)"
          if [ "$type" == "" ] ; then
            echo "Resource type not found in $r, creating"
            aws cloudformation create-stack --stack-name awsqs-eks-cluster --template-body file://eks-deploy.template.yaml --parameters ParameterKey=CreateClusterAccessRole,ParameterValue=Disabled --capabilities CAPABILITY_NAMED_IAM --region $r
          else
            echo "Resource type $type found in region $r"
          fi
        done
      - |
        echo "waiting for AWSQS::EKS::Cluster resource type registration to complete..."
        for r in ${REGIONS}; do
          if [ "$(aws cloudformation list-types --region $r --query 'TypeSummaries[?TypeName==`AWSQS::EKS::Cluster`].TypeName' --output text)" == "" ] ; then
            aws cloudformation wait stack-create-complete --stack-name awsqs-eks-cluster --region ${r}
          fi
        done
      - |
        echo "deleting any old prereq stacks..."
        for r in ${REGIONS}; do
          aws cloudformation delete-stack --stack-name helm-resource-provider-contract-tests --region ${r}
        done
      - |
        echo "creating vpc stacks..."
        for r in ${REGIONS}; do
          echo $r
          vpc="$(aws cloudformation list-exports --region us-east-1 --query 'Exports[?Name==`helm-resource-provider-contract-tests-vpc-VPCCIDR`]' --output text)"
          if [ "$vpc"  == "" ]; then
            echo "VPC not found in $r, creating"
            aws cloudformation create-stack --stack-name helm-resource-provider-contract-tests-vpc \
              --template-url https://aws-quickstart.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/quickstart-aws-vpc/templates/aws-vpc.template \
              --region ${r} \
              --parameters \
                ParameterKey=AvailabilityZones,ParameterValue="\"${r}a,${r}b\"" \
                ParameterKey=NumberOfAZs,ParameterValue=2 \
                ParameterKey=VPCCIDR,ParameterValue=10.0.0.0/16 \
                ParameterKey=PublicSubnet1CIDR,ParameterValue=10.0.10.0/24 \
                ParameterKey=PublicSubnet2CIDR,ParameterValue=10.0.11.0/24 \
                ParameterKey=PrivateSubnet1ACIDR,ParameterValue=10.0.0.0/24 \
                ParameterKey=PrivateSubnet2ACIDR,ParameterValue=10.0.1.0/24 \
                ParameterKey=PublicSubnetTag2,ParameterValue=kubernetes.io/role/elb= \
                ParameterKey=PrivateSubnetATag2,ParameterValue=kubernetes.io/role/internal-elb=
          else
            echo "Found VPC $vpc in region $r"
          fi
        done
      - |
        echo "waiting for vpc stacks to complete..."
        for r in ${REGIONS}; do
          aws cloudformation wait stack-create-complete --stack-name helm-resource-provider-contract-tests-vpc --region ${r}
        done
      - |
        echo "waiting for any old prereq stacks to delete..."
        for r in ${REGIONS}; do
          aws cloudformation wait stack-delete-complete --stack-name helm-resource-provider-contract-tests --region ${r}
        done
      - |
        echo "creating prereq stacks..."
        for r in ${REGIONS}; do
          echo "Creating prereq stack on $r"
          aws cloudformation create-stack --stack-name helm-resource-provider-contract-tests \
            --template-body file://contract_test_exports.template.yaml --capabilities CAPABILITY_IAM --region ${r}
        done
      - |
        echo "waiting for prereq stacks to complete..."
        for r in ${REGIONS}; do
          aws cloudformation wait stack-create-complete --stack-name helm-resource-provider-contract-tests --region ${r}
        done
      - cd ../
      - |
        set -ex
        published=
        for t in ${BUILD_DIRS}; do
          echo $t
          cd ${t}
          go mod download
          TYPE_NAME=$(jq -r .typeName .rpdk-config)
          TYPE_NAME_LOWER=$(echo ${TYPE_NAME} | tr [:upper:] [:lower:] | sed 's/::/-/g')
          make -f Makefile.package
          rolearn=$(aws cloudformation describe-stacks --stack-name helm-resource-provider-contract-tests --region ${r} --query 'Stacks[0].Outputs[?OutputKey==`HelmRoleArn`].OutputValue' --output text)
          for r in ${REGIONS}; do
            if [ "$rolearn" == "" ] || [ "$rolearn" == "None" ]; then
              echo "Can't register custom type in region $r, role is '$rolearn'"
            else
              echo "Registering custom type in region $r with role $rolearn"
              REGION=${r} \
                TYPE_NAME=${TYPE_NAME}
                BUCKET=${BUCKET} \
                EX_ROLE="$rolearn" \
                LOG_ROLE="$rolearn" \
                make register 
              aws s3 rm --recursive s3://${BUCKET}/CloudFormation/ContractTestResults/${TYPE_NAME}/ || true
              ARN=$(aws cloudformation describe-type --type RESOURCE --type-name "${TYPE_NAME}" --region ${r} --query Arn --output text)
              aws uno test-type --type RESOURCE --arn ${ARN} --region ${r} --log-delivery-bucket ${BUCKET}
            fi
          done
          cd ../
        done
        echo "Custom type ready to be published in regions: $published"
        for t in ${BUILD_DIRS}; do
          echo $t
          cd ${t}
          TYPE_NAME=$(jq -r .typeName .rpdk-config)
          TYPE_NAME_LOWER=$(echo ${TYPE_NAME} | tr [:upper:] [:lower:] | sed 's/::/-/g')
          for r in ${REGIONS}; do
            echo "Checking status of type in region $r"
            ARN=$(aws cloudformation describe-type --type RESOURCE --type-name "${TYPE_NAME}" --region ${r} --query Arn --output text)
            while [ "$(aws uno describe-type --arn ${ARN} --region ${r} --query TypeTestsStatus --output text)" == "IN_PROGRESS" ] ; do sleep 60 ; done
            STATUS=$(aws uno describe-type --arn ${ARN} --region ${r} --query TypeTestsStatus --output text)
            if [ "${STATUS}" == "FAILED" ] ; then
              echo "${TYPE_NAME} tests failed: $(aws uno describe-type --arn ${ARN} --region ${r} --query TypeTestsStatusDescription)"
              ZIP_PATH=$(aws s3 ls --recursive s3://${BUCKET}/CloudFormation/ContractTestResults/${TYPE_NAME}/ | awk '{print $4}')
              mkdir /tmp/logs/
              for ZIP_FILE in ${ZIP_PATH}; do
                rm -rf /tmp/logs/*
                aws s3 cp s3://${BUCKET}/${ZIP_FILE} /tmp/logs/logs.zip
                gunzip -d -S .zip /tmp/logs/logs.zip
                echo ""
                echo ""
                echo "================================TestType Logs================================"
                echo "${ZIP_FILE}"
                cat /tmp/logs/*
                echo "==============================End TestType Logs=============================="
                echo ""
                echo ""
              done
              aws s3 rm --recursive s3://${BUCKET}/CloudFormation/ContractTestResults/${TYPE_NAME}/
              exit 1
            else
              if [ "${PUBLISH}" == "true" ] ; then
                myarn=$(echo ${ARN} | awk 'BEGIN{FS=OFS="/"}{NF--; print}')
                echo "Publishing custom type $myarn on region $r"
                fail=0
                ( aws uno publish-type --arn "${myarn}" --region "${r}" ) || fail=$?
                if [ $fail -ne 0 ]; then
                  echo "Code $fail, could not publish custom type with arn ${myarn} on region ${r}"
                else
                  echo "Published custom type with arn ${myarn} on region ${r}"
                  published="$r $published"
                fi
              else
                echo "Skipping publish, as PUBLISH env var is not set to true"
              fi
            fi
          done
        done
        echo "Custom type published in regions: $published"
  post_build:
    commands:
      - |
          echo "deleting prereq stacks..."
          for r in ${REGIONS}; do
            echo "Region: ${r}"
            aws cloudformation delete-stack --stack-name helm-resource-provider-contract-tests --region ${r}
          done
